Introduction

A.KOR was a three-member girl group under Doo Republic. They first debuted on July 25, 2014 as a trio unit with the single "Payday" and before making their official debut with five-members on September 5, 2014 with the single "But Go".

In June 2015, they debuted its first sub-unit A.KOR Black consisting of members Minju and Kemy.

They silently disbanded in 2017 due to inactivity.
